{"title_page": "Philippe Martinez (trade unionist)", "text_new": "{{short description|French trade unionist}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n | honorific_prefix   = \n | name               = Philippe Martinez\n | native_name        = <!--The person's name in their own language, if different.-->\n | native_name_lang   = <!--ISO 639-1 code, e.g., \"fr\" for French. If more than one, use {{lang}} in |native_name= instead.-->\n | honorific_suffix   = \n | image              = PhilippeMartinez.jpg\n | image_size         = \n | image_upright      = \n | smallimage         = <!--If this is specified, \"image\" should not be.-->\n | alt                = \n | caption            = Philippe Martinez in 2015\n | order              = \n | office             = General Secretary of the [[General Confederation of Labour (France)|General Confederation of Labour]]\n | status             = <!--If this is specified, overrides Incumbent.-->\n | term_start         = February 3, 2015\n | term_end           = \n | alongside          = \n | deputy             = \n | predecessor        = [[Thierry Lepaon]]\n | successor          = \n |birth_date={{birth date and age|1961|04|01}}\n |birth_place=[[Suresnes]], [[Seine (department)|Seine]]\n |nationality=French\n |alma_mater=\n |occupation=Technician in the metalworking industry\n}}\n\n'''Philippe Martinez''' (born 1 April 1961 in [[Suresnes]], [[Seine (department)|Seine department]]) is a French [[trade unionist]]. He has been the general secretary of the [[General Confederation of Labour (France)|General Confederation of Labour]] (CGT) since 2015.\n\n==Biography==\n===Early life===\nHis father, born at {{ill|La Plaine Saint-Denis|fr}} in France, fought in the [[International Brigades]] during the [[Spanish Civil War]] in 1936.<ref name=\"nouvelobs20151019\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Denis |last=Demonpion |title=Moustache et lutte des classes : 10 choses \u00e0 savoir sur Philippe Martinez, le patron de la CGT|url=http://tempsreel.nouvelobs.com/societe/social/20150211.OBS2232/moustache-et-lutte-des-classes-10-choses-a-savoir-sur-philippe-martinez-le-patron-de-la-cgt.html |date=October 19, 2015 |newspaper=[[Le Nouvel Obs]]}}</ref><ref name=\"vsd20160524\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Christelle |last=Briere |title=Blocage-essence. Qui est vraiment Philippe Martinez, le patron de la CGT\u202f? |url=http://www.vsd.fr/actualite/blocage-essence.-qui-est-vraiment-philippe-martinez-le-patron-de-la-cgt-videos-13552 |date=May 24, 2016|newspaper=[[VSD (magazine)|VSD]]}}</ref><ref name=\"liberation20150311\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Amandine |last=Cailhol|url=http://www.liberation.fr/futurs/2015/03/11/philippe-martinez-nouveau-velu_1218794 |title=Philippe Martinez. Nouveau velu |date=March 11, 2011 |newspaper=[[Lib\u00e9ration]] }}</ref> Philippe Martinez's mother comes from [[Santander, Spain|Santander]] in northern [[Spain]].<ref name=\"nouvelobs20151019\"/><ref name=\"liberation20150311\"/>\n\nPhilippe Martinez attended school in [[Rueil-Malmaison]], west of Paris.<ref name=lexpress>{{cite web|language=fr|url=https://lexpansion.lexpress.fr/actualite-economique/cgt-philippe-martinez-la-gueule-de-l-emploi_1669145.html|title=CGT: Philippe Martinez, la gueule de l'emploi|first=Agn\u00e8s |last=Laurent|date=April 13, 2015|website=lexpansion.lexpress.fr|access-date=January 12, 2018}}</ref> He engaged into politics as a high school student, first joining the [[Mouvement Jeunes Communistes de France|Young Communist Movement]] and later the [[French Communist Party]].<ref name=\"vsd20160524\"/><ref name=\"liberation20150311\"/><ref name=\"capital20160525\">{{cite news|language=fr|url=http://www.capital.fr/a-la-une/politique-economique/ce-que-nous-savez-surement-pas-sur-philippe-martinez-l-homme-fort-de-la-cgt-1131557 |title=Ce que nous savez s\u00fbrement pas sur Philippe Martinez, l\u2019homme fort de la CGT|newspaper=[[Capital (magazine)|Capital]]|date=May 25, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Professional career===\nA technician in the metalworking industry, he worked for the [[\u00cele Seguin|Renault factory]] of [[Boulogne-Billancourt]] from 1982,<ref name=\"Le Monde_3/2/2014\">{{cite news|language=fr |title=Philippe Martinez \u00e9lu secr\u00e9taire g\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la CGT |url=http://abonnes.lemonde.fr/economie/article/2015/02/03/philippe-martinez-elu-secretaire-general-de-la-cgt_4568954_3234.html  |newspaper=[[Le Monde]] |date=February 3, 2015}}</ref> before he was transferred to the Center for Motor Research at Rueil-Malmaison.<ref name=\"lhumanite20150204\">{{cite news|language=fr|first1=Yves |last1=Housson |title=Philippe Martinez De Billancourt \u00e0 Montreuil, parcours d\u2019un m\u00e9tallo |url=https://www.humanite.fr/philippe-martinez-de-billancourt-montreuil-parcours-dun-metallo-564643 |newspaper=[[L'Humanit\u00e9]]|date=February 4, 2015}}</ref>\n\nA union member since 1984,<ref name=fig>{{cite news|language=fr|first=C\u00e9cile |last=Crouzel|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/social/2016/05/25/09010-20160525ARTFIG00344-philippe-martinez-l-homme-qui-veut-mettre-la-france-a-genoux.php|title=Philippe Martinez, l'homme qui veut mettre la France \u00e0 genoux|newspaper=[[Le Figaro]]|date=May 25, 2016|access-date=}}</ref> he became the [[General Confederation of Labour (France)|CGT]] central union delegate at [[Renault]].<ref name=\"Figaro13012015\">{{cite news|first=C\u00e9cile |last=Crouzel|title=Philippe Martinez, nouvel homme cl\u00e9 de la CGT|newspaper=[[Le Figaro]]|date=January 13, 2015|issn=0182-5852|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/social/2015/01/12/09010-20150112ARTFIG00344-philippe-martinez-nouvel-homme-cle-de-la-cgt.php}}</ref>\n\nHe left the French Communist Party in 2002 since he disagreed with [[Robert Hue]] who wanted to disestablish the Party's sections inside the companies.<ref name=\"lesechos20150203\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Le\u00efla |last=de Comarmond|title=CGT : Philippe Martinez, un pragmatique qui cultive une image de dur|newspaper=[[Les Echos (France)|Les \u00c9chos]]|date=February 3, 2015|issn=0153-4831|url=https://www.lesechos.fr/economie-france/social/0204126339461-un-pragmatique-qui-cultive-une-image-de-dur-1089509.php}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, Martinez was elected general secretary of the [[Metalworkers' Federation]] (FTM-CGT),<ref name=\"Le Monde_3/2/2014\"/> the third largest federation within the CGT with 60,000 members.<ref name=\"Le Monde\">{{cite web|language=fr|url=http://abonnes.lemonde.fr/politique/article/2015/02/03/philippe-martinez-un-metallo-a-la-tete-de-la-cgt_4569171_823448.html|author=[[Agence France-Presse|AFP]]|title=Philippe Martinez, un \" m\u00e9tallo \" \u00e0 la t\u00eate de la CGT|newspaper=[[Le Monde]]|date=February 3, 2015|access-date=February 3, 2015}}.</ref> In this respect, he negotiated with the employers within the scope of the reorganisation of the automotive industry, thus showing his ability to discuss by containing the most radical elements of his union.<ref name=fig/>\n\nIn 2013, he was elected a member of the CGT executive committee.<ref name=\"Le Monde_3/2/2014\"/>\n\n===General secretary of the CGT===\nEven if he was foreseen to become the general secretary of the union, Martinez was unknown to the public.<ref>{{cite web|language=fr|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/societe/thierry-lepaon/philippe-martinez-le-futur-boss-de-la-cgt-un-moustachu-tres-discret_813979.html|first=Pierre |last=Godon|title=Moustache, myst\u00e8re et main de fer : qui est Philippe Martinez, le nouveau secr\u00e9taire g\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la CGT ?|publisher=[[France T\u00e9l\u00e9visions]]|date=February 4, 2015|access-date=February 9, 2015}}</ref> Even though his team was seen as too close to the previous leading team, it was elected with 57.5 percent of the votes of the National Confederal Committee. Martinez's partner Nathalie Gamiochipi, who was appointed to call for votes against Martinez, decided to support him with the votes of the [[CGT Sant\u00e9]],<ref name=lexpress/><ref>{{cite news|language=fr|first=Leila |last=de Comarmond|url=https://www.lesechos.fr/27/03/2015/lesechos.fr/0204260391781_cgt-sante---la-direction-sortante-balayee.htm |title=CGT sant\u00e9 : la direction sortante balay\u00e9e|newspaper=[[Les Echos (France)|Les Echos]]|date=March 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|language=fr|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/economie/cgt-la-compagne-de-martinez-limogee-28-03-2015-4645683.php |title=CGT : la compagne de Martinez, le nouveau patron, limog\u00e9e|newspaper=[[Le Parisien]]|date=March 28, 2015}}</ref> the second largest federation of the CGT with 75,000 members. Martinez was elected general secretary of the CGT<ref name=\"Le Monde_3/2/2014\"/> by the National Confederal Committee on February 3, 2015 with 93.4 percent of the votes,<ref name=lexpress/> and was confirmed to that position by the congress of Marseille in April 2016, after he travelled across France during one year to meet the local sections of the union to strengthen his popularity.<ref name=fig/>\n\nEven though Martinez embodies the grassroots and the radical line of the union,<ref name=lexpress/> he is open for labour relations and supportive of the traditional strategy of the union, according to newspapers ''[[Le Figaro]]'' and ''[[Lib\u00e9ration]]''.<ref name=\"Figaro13012015\"/><ref>{{cite news|language=fr|first1=Fr\u00e9d\u00e9rique |last1=Roussel |first2=Luc |last2=Peillon|title=Philippe Martinez, un orthodoxe \u00e0 la barre de la CGT|newspaper=[[Lib\u00e9ration]]|date=February 3, 2015|issn=0335-1793|url=http://www.liberation.fr/economie/2015/02/03/philippe-martinez-un-orthodoxe-a-la-barre-de-la-cgt_1194673}}</ref> However, according to ''[[Les Echos (France)|Les Echos]]'', Martinez being no longer a member of the Communist Party since 2002, he has been the \"first [such] general secretary of the CGT since 1946\", which shows a \"a further step in the detachment of both organisations\", even though Martinez did not become supportive of [[social-democracy]].<ref name=\"lesechos20150203\"/><ref>\u00c0 partir de 1945, [[L\u00e9on Jouhaux]] partage la fonction de secr\u00e9taire g\u00e9n\u00e9ral avec le communiste [[Beno\u00eet Frachon]], \u00e0 qui il remet sa d\u00e9mission le 19 d\u00e9cembre 1947 : voir {{cite journal|language = fr|first= Dominique |last=Andolfatto|title = Les syndicats en France|journal= \u00c9tudes de la Documentation fran\u00e7aise|issue = 5260|year = 2007|issn = |url = //books.google.fr/books?id=ztILAQAAMAAJ}}</ref> Moreover, Martinez is the first technician, not worker, to lead the union.\n\n[[File:Philippe Martinez.jpg|thumb|Philippe Martinez in 2017.|225px]]\nTo take account of the growing influence of the [[ultra-left]] in the union, Martinez took on a hard line of struggle against employers and [[economic liberalism|liberalism]], notably against the [[Second Valls government|Valls government]] by demanding the withdrawal of the [[El Khomri law|2016 Labour reform bill]], to which the CGT became the main opponent.<ref name=fig/> Demonstrations were accompanied by blockades of refineries, repetitive strikes in the transport sector, and stoppage of nuclear power plants, which threatened the smooth running of the [[UEFA Euro 2016]] in France.<ref name=fig/> The Filpac-CGT (Federation of Workers of the Book, Paper and Communications Industry), demanded that all national daily newspapers publish a column of Philippe Martinez \u2014called {{lang|fr|La modernit\u00e9, c\u2019est le progr\u00e8s social, pas la loi travail !}} (\"Modernity is Social Progress, not Labour Law!\")\u2014, for them to be printed out.<ref name=\"liberation20160526\">{{cite news|language=fr|title=Comment la Filpac-CGT a bloqu\u00e9 la parution des journaux nationaux jeudi|newspaper=Lib\u00e9ration|date=May 26, 2016|url=http://www.liberation.fr/futurs/2016/05/26/comment-la-filpac-cgt-a-bloque-la-parution-des-journaux-nationaux-jeudi_1455346}}</ref><ref name=\"marianne20160526\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Thomas|last=Vampouille|title=Apr\u00e8s l'\u00e9chec de son chantage, la CGT bloque les quotidiens nationaux|newspaper=[[Marianne (magazine)|Marianne]]|date=May 26, 2016|url=https://www.marianne.net/apres-echec-son-chantage-cgt-bloque-les-quotidiens-nationaux-100243150.html}}</ref> Only the newspaper ''[[L'Humanit\u00e9]]'' published the tribune,<ref name=\"lefigaro20160526\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Alexandre |last=Debout\u00e9 |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/medias/2016/05/26/20004-20160526ARTFIG00085-les-quotidiens-nationaux-victimes-d-un-chantage-de-la-cgt.php |title=Les quotidiens nationaux victimes d'un chantage de la CGT |newspaper=[[Le Figaro]] |date=May 26, 2016}}</ref> and the Filipac voted a strike to stop printing the newspapers, which aroused criticism from newspaper leaders and the national daily press union (SPQN), in the name of [[freedom of the press]].<ref name=\"mediapart20160526\">{{cite news|language=fr|first1=Mathilde|last1=Goanec|first2=Micha\u00ebl|last2=Hajdenberg|first3=Dan|last3=Israel|title=Libert\u00e9 de la presse: la CGT n'imprime pas|newspaper=[[Mediapart]]|date=May 26, 2016|url=https://www.mediapart.fr/journal/france/260516/liberte-de-la-presse-la-cgt-nimprime-pas}}</ref><ref name=\"lepoint20160526\">{{cite news|language=fr|title=Pourquoi la CGT emp\u00eache la presse de para\u00eetre|newspaper=[[Le Point]]|date=May 26, 2016|url=http://www.lepoint.fr/medias/pourquoi-la-cgt-empeche-la-presse-de-paraitre-26-05-2016-2042218_260.php}}</ref><ref name=\"valeuractuelles20160526\">{{cite news|language=fr|url=https://www.valeursactuelles.com/societe/censure-de-la-presse-la-cgt-en-pleine-derive-dictatoriale-62155 |title=Censure de la presse : la CGT en pleine d\u00e9rive dictatoriale  |newspaper=[[Valeurs actuelles]]|date=May 26, 2016}}</ref>\n\nFaced with the internal oppositions and the decreasing importance of the CGT in the staff representatives elections, this anti-establishment opinion could enable the union to unify the militants and draw benefit from the left-wing voters' dissatisfaction toward the [[Socialist Party (France)|Socialist Party]] government.<ref name=fig/>\n\nMartinez was re-elected as the general secretary of the CGT during the union's 51st congress in Marseille in April 2016.<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|title=Philippe Martinez r\u00e9\u00e9lu \u00e0 la t\u00eate d'une \"CGT d\u00e9termin\u00e9e\"|url=http://www.liberation.fr/france/2016/04/22/philippe-martinez-reelu-a-la-tete-d-une-cgt-determinee_1447915|date=April 22, 2016|access-date=August 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\nUnder Martinez's chairmanship, in March 2017, the CGT became the second most important union in the [[private sector]] after the [[French Democratic Confederation of Labour]] (CFDT).<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/social/2017/03/31/20011-20170331ARTFIG00091-la-cfdt-pourrait-detroner-la-cgt-et-devenir-le-premier-syndicat-national.php |title=La CFDT d\u00e9tr\u00f4ne la CGT et devient le premier syndicat national dans le priv\u00e9|newspaper=[[Le Figaro]]|date=March 31, 2017}}</ref> However, it remained the largest union in small businesses and in the [[French Civil Service|Civil Service]] and therefore remained the largest organisation among all wage earners.<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|author=|title=Repr\u00e9sentativit\u00e9 syndicale (CGT)|newspaper=[[L'Humanit\u00e9]]|date=March 31, 2017|issn=|url=https://www.humanite.fr/representativite-syndicale-cgt-634179|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nUnder Martinez's direction, the CGT organised a 36-day strike in the first semester 2018 against the government's reform plans of the [[SNCF]].<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|title=Martinez: gr\u00e8ve \"massive\" \u00e0 la SNCF, il faut \"repartir d'une feuille blanche\"|newspaper=[[L'Express]]|date=April 3, 2018|url=https://www.lexpress.fr/actualites/1/politique/martinez-greve-massive-a-la-sncf-il-faut-repartir-d-une-feuille-blanche_1997179.html|access-date=April 3, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019, Martinez was re-elected general secretary of the CGT during the 52nd congress in [[Dijon]]. He was the only candidate to his own succession and was re-elected with 90.65 percent of votes.<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|url=https://www.liberation.fr/france/2019/05/17/reelu-a-la-tete-de-la-cgt-philippe-martinez-appelle-au-rassemblement_1727621 |newspaper=[[Lib\u00e9ration]]|date=May 17, 2019 |title=R\u00e9\u00e9lu \u00e0 la t\u00eate de la CGT Philippe Martinez appelle au \" rassemblement \"|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Opinions==\nWhen he was elected the general secretary of the CGT, Martinez proposed to reduce the weekly work time to 32 hours to enable the creation of four million new jobs.<ref name=\"rtl20150206\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Fran\u00e7ois |last=Lenglet |author-link=Fran\u00e7ois Lenglet |title=Travail : le leader de la CGT Philippe Martinez plaide pour la semaine de 32 heures |url=http://www.rtl.fr/actu/economie/travail-le-leader-de-la-cgt-philippe-martinez-plaide-pour-la-semaine-de-32-heures-7776493619 |date=February 6, 2015 |publisher=[[RTL (French radio)|RTL]]}}</ref><ref name=\"challenges20150205\">{{cite news|language=fr|title=A peine \u00e9lu \u00e0 la t\u00eate de la CGT, Philippe Martinez plaide pour les 32 heures |url=https://www.challenges.fr/economie/20150205.CHA2809/a-peine-elu-a-la-tete-de-la-cgt-philippe-martinez-plaide-pour-les-32-heures.html |newspaper=[[Challenges (magazine)|Challenges]] |date=February 5, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|language=fr|title=Pour la CGT, passer \u00e0 32 heures est une n\u00e9cessit\u00e9|url=https://www.humanite.fr/pour-la-cgt-passer-32-heures-est-une-necessite-586757|date=October 13, 2015|access-date=August 13, 2016}}</ref> He also supports a \u20ac1800 gross monthly [[minimum wage]], a 60 years old retirement age, and opposes the payment of [[dividends]] to shareholders.<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/politique/article/2019/05/13/martinez-met-en-garde-une-cgt-qui-ne-doit-pas-se-refermer-sur-elle-meme_5461624_823448.html|title=Philippe Martinez met en garde une CGT qui \" ne doit pas se refermer sur elle-m\u00eame \"|newspaper=[[Le Monde]]|date=May 13, 2019|access-date=December 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\nBetween the two rounds of the [[2017 French presidential election]] between [[Emmanuel Macron]] and [[Marine Le Pen]], Martinez claimed he wanted \"Macron to have the highest possible score\" against the [[National Front (France)|National Front]] candidate, thereby overstepping the original position of the GGT.<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/election-presidentielle-2017/article/2017/05/05/martinez-souhaite-que-macron-fasse-le-score-le-plus-haut-possible_5123118_4854003.html |title=Martinez souhaite que \u00ab Macron fasse le score le plus haut possible|newspaper=Le Monde|date=May 5, 2017|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nMartinez supported the welcoming of [[Immigration|migrants]] several time: for instance in 2018, he claimed that it was France's \"duty\" to \"welcome them all\" and considered as \"scandalous\" the government's decision to distinguish [[economic migrant]]s from [[refugees]].<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|url=http://information.tv5monde.com/en-continu/migrants-il-faut-les-accueillir-tous-pour-martinez-214334 |title=Migrants: il faut \"les accueillir tous\" pour Martinez|website=tv5monde.com|date=January 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Private life==\nMartinez lives with Nathalie Gamiochipi, former general secretary of the [[CGT Sant\u00e9]], the second largest federation of the CGT with 75,000 members.<ref name=\"nouvelobs20151019\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Portal|Organised labour|France}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Philippe Martinez}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Martinez, Philippe}}\n[[Category:Members of the General Confederation of Labour (France)]]\n[[Category:Trade union leaders]]\n[[Category:People from Suresnes]]\n[[Category:French people of Spanish descent]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French trade unionist}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n | honorific_prefix   = \n | name               = Philippe Martinez\n | native_name        = <!--The person's name in their own language, if different.-->\n | native_name_lang   = <!--ISO 639-1 code, e.g., \"fr\" for French. If more than one, use {{lang}} in |native_name= instead.-->\n | honorific_suffix   = \n | image              = PhilippeMartinez.jpg\n | image_size         = \n | image_upright      = \n | smallimage         = <!--If this is specified, \"image\" should not be.-->\n | alt                = \n | caption            = Philippe Martinez in 2015\n | order              = \n | office             = General Secretary of the [[General Confederation of Labour (France)|General Confederation of Labour]]\n | status             = <!--If this is specified, overrides Incumbent.-->\n | term_start         = February 3, 2015\n | term_end           = \n | alongside          = \n | deputy             = \n | predecessor        = [[Thierry Lepaon]]\n | successor          = \n |birth_date={{birth date and age|1961|04|01}}\n |birth_place=[[Suresnes]], [[Seine (department)|Seine]]\n |nationality=French\n |alma_mater=\n |occupation=Technician in the metalworking industry\n}}\n\n'''Philippe Martinez''' (born 1 April 1961 in [[Suresnes]], [[Seine (department)|Seine department]]) is a French [[trade unionist]]. He has been the general secretary of the [[General Confederation of Labour (France)|General Confederation of Labour]] (CGT) since 2015.\n\n==Biography==\n===Early life===\nHis father, born at {{ill|La Plaine Saint-Denis|fr}} in France, fought in the [[International Brigades]] during the [[Spanish Civil War]] in 1936.<ref name=\"nouvelobs20151019\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Denis |last=Demonpion |title=Moustache et lutte des classes : 10 choses \u00e0 savoir sur Philippe Martinez, le patron de la CGT|url=http://tempsreel.nouvelobs.com/societe/social/20150211.OBS2232/moustache-et-lutte-des-classes-10-choses-a-savoir-sur-philippe-martinez-le-patron-de-la-cgt.html |date=October 19, 2015 |newspaper=[[Le Nouvel Obs]]}}</ref><ref name=\"vsd20160524\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Christelle |last=Briere |title=Blocage-essence. Qui est vraiment Philippe Martinez, le patron de la CGT\u202f? |url=http://www.vsd.fr/actualite/blocage-essence.-qui-est-vraiment-philippe-martinez-le-patron-de-la-cgt-videos-13552 |date=May 24, 2016|newspaper=[[VSD (magazine)|VSD]]}}</ref><ref name=\"liberation20150311\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Amandine |last=Cailhol|url=http://www.liberation.fr/futurs/2015/03/11/philippe-martinez-nouveau-velu_1218794 |title=Philippe Martinez. Nouveau velu |date=March 11, 2011 |newspaper=[[Lib\u00e9ration]] }}</ref> Philippe Martinez's mother comes from [[Santander, Spain|Santander]] in northern [[Spain]].<ref name=\"nouvelobs20151019\"/><ref name=\"liberation20150311\"/>\n\nPhilippe Martinez attended school in [[Rueil-Malmaison]], west of Paris.<ref name=lexpress>{{cite web|language=fr|url=https://lexpansion.lexpress.fr/actualite-economique/cgt-philippe-martinez-la-gueule-de-l-emploi_1669145.html|title=CGT: Philippe Martinez, la gueule de l'emploi|first=Agn\u00e8s |last=Laurent|date=April 13, 2015|website=lexpansion.lexpress.fr|access-date=January 12, 2018}}</ref> He engaged into politics as a high school student, first joining the [[Mouvement Jeunes Communistes de France|Young Communist Movement]] and later the [[French Communist Party]].<ref name=\"vsd20160524\"/><ref name=\"liberation20150311\"/><ref name=\"capital20160525\">{{cite news|language=fr|url=http://www.capital.fr/a-la-une/politique-economique/ce-que-nous-savez-surement-pas-sur-philippe-martinez-l-homme-fort-de-la-cgt-1131557 |title=Ce que nous savez s\u00fbrement pas sur Philippe Martinez, l\u2019homme fort de la CGT|newspaper=[[Capital (magazine)|Capital]]|date=May 25, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Professional career===\nA technician in the metalworking industry, he worked for the [[\u00cele Seguin|Renault factory]] of [[Boulogne-Billancourt]] from 1982,<ref name=\"Le Monde_3/2/2014\">{{cite news|language=fr |title=Philippe Martinez \u00e9lu secr\u00e9taire g\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la CGT |url=http://abonnes.lemonde.fr/economie/article/2015/02/03/philippe-martinez-elu-secretaire-general-de-la-cgt_4568954_3234.html  |newspaper=[[Le Monde]] |date=February 3, 2015}}</ref> before he was transferred to the Center for Motor Research at Rueil-Malmaison.<ref name=\"lhumanite20150204\">{{cite news|language=fr|first1=Yves |last1=Housson |title=Philippe Martinez De Billancourt \u00e0 Montreuil, parcours d\u2019un m\u00e9tallo |url=https://www.humanite.fr/philippe-martinez-de-billancourt-montreuil-parcours-dun-metallo-564643 |newspaper=[[L'Humanit\u00e9]]|date=February 4, 2015}}</ref>\n\nA union member since 1984,<ref name=fig>{{cite news|language=fr|first=C\u00e9cile |last=Crouzel|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/social/2016/05/25/09010-20160525ARTFIG00344-philippe-martinez-l-homme-qui-veut-mettre-la-france-a-genoux.php|title=Philippe Martinez, l'homme qui veut mettre la France \u00e0 genoux|newspaper=[[Le Figaro]]|date=May 25, 2016|access-date=}}</ref> he became the [[General Confederation of Labour (France)|CGT]] central union delegate at [[Renault]].<ref name=\"Figaro13012015\">{{cite news|first=C\u00e9cile |last=Crouzel|title=Philippe Martinez, nouvel homme cl\u00e9 de la CGT|newspaper=[[Le Figaro]]|date=January 13, 2015|issn=0182-5852|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/social/2015/01/12/09010-20150112ARTFIG00344-philippe-martinez-nouvel-homme-cle-de-la-cgt.php}}</ref>\n\nHe left the French Communist Party in 2002 since he disagreed with [[Robert Hue]] who wanted to disestablish the Party's sections inside the companies.<ref name=\"lesechos20150203\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Le\u00efla |last=de Comarmond|title=CGT : Philippe Martinez, un pragmatique qui cultive une image de dur|newspaper=[[Les Echos (France)|Les \u00c9chos]]|date=February 3, 2015|issn=0153-4831|url=https://www.lesechos.fr/economie-france/social/0204126339461-un-pragmatique-qui-cultive-une-image-de-dur-1089509.php}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, Martinez was elected general secretary of the [[CGT Steelworkers' Federation (France)|CGT Steelworkers' Federation]] (FTM-CGT),<ref name=\"Le Monde_3/2/2014\"/> the third largest federation within the CGT with 60,000 members.<ref name=\"Le Monde\">{{cite web|language=fr|url=http://abonnes.lemonde.fr/politique/article/2015/02/03/philippe-martinez-un-metallo-a-la-tete-de-la-cgt_4569171_823448.html|author=[[Agence France-Presse|AFP]]|title=Philippe Martinez, un \" m\u00e9tallo \" \u00e0 la t\u00eate de la CGT|newspaper=[[Le Monde]]|date=February 3, 2015|access-date=February 3, 2015}}.</ref> In this respect, he negotiated with the employers within the scope of the reorganisation of the automotive industry, thus showing his ability to discuss by containing the most radical elements of his union.<ref name=fig/>\n\nIn 2013, he was elected a member of the CGT executive committee.<ref name=\"Le Monde_3/2/2014\"/>\n\n===General secretary of the CGT===\nEven if he was foreseen to become the general secretary of the union, Martinez was unknown to the public.<ref>{{cite web|language=fr|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/societe/thierry-lepaon/philippe-martinez-le-futur-boss-de-la-cgt-un-moustachu-tres-discret_813979.html|first=Pierre |last=Godon|title=Moustache, myst\u00e8re et main de fer : qui est Philippe Martinez, le nouveau secr\u00e9taire g\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la CGT ?|publisher=[[France T\u00e9l\u00e9visions]]|date=February 4, 2015|access-date=February 9, 2015}}</ref> Even though his team was seen as too close to the previous leading team, it was elected with 57.5 percent of the votes of the National Confederal Committee. Martinez's partner Nathalie Gamiochipi, who was appointed to call for votes against Martinez, decided to support him with the votes of the [[CGT Sant\u00e9]],<ref name=lexpress/><ref>{{cite news|language=fr|first=Leila |last=de Comarmond|url=https://www.lesechos.fr/27/03/2015/lesechos.fr/0204260391781_cgt-sante---la-direction-sortante-balayee.htm |title=CGT sant\u00e9 : la direction sortante balay\u00e9e|newspaper=[[Les Echos (France)|Les Echos]]|date=March 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|language=fr|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/economie/cgt-la-compagne-de-martinez-limogee-28-03-2015-4645683.php |title=CGT : la compagne de Martinez, le nouveau patron, limog\u00e9e|newspaper=[[Le Parisien]]|date=March 28, 2015}}</ref> the second largest federation of the CGT with 75,000 members. Martinez was elected general secretary of the CGT<ref name=\"Le Monde_3/2/2014\"/> by the National Confederal Committee on February 3, 2015 with 93.4 percent of the votes,<ref name=lexpress/> and was confirmed to that position by the congress of Marseille in April 2016, after he travelled across France during one year to meet the local sections of the union to strengthen his popularity.<ref name=fig/>\n\nEven though Martinez embodies the grassroots and the radical line of the union,<ref name=lexpress/> he is open for labour relations and supportive of the traditional strategy of the union, according to newspapers ''[[Le Figaro]]'' and ''[[Lib\u00e9ration]]''.<ref name=\"Figaro13012015\"/><ref>{{cite news|language=fr|first1=Fr\u00e9d\u00e9rique |last1=Roussel |first2=Luc |last2=Peillon|title=Philippe Martinez, un orthodoxe \u00e0 la barre de la CGT|newspaper=[[Lib\u00e9ration]]|date=February 3, 2015|issn=0335-1793|url=http://www.liberation.fr/economie/2015/02/03/philippe-martinez-un-orthodoxe-a-la-barre-de-la-cgt_1194673}}</ref> However, according to ''[[Les Echos (France)|Les Echos]]'', Martinez being no longer a member of the Communist Party since 2002, he has been the \"first [such] general secretary of the CGT since 1946\", which shows a \"a further step in the detachment of both organisations\", even though Martinez did not become supportive of [[social-democracy]].<ref name=\"lesechos20150203\"/><ref>\u00c0 partir de 1945, [[L\u00e9on Jouhaux]] partage la fonction de secr\u00e9taire g\u00e9n\u00e9ral avec le communiste [[Beno\u00eet Frachon]], \u00e0 qui il remet sa d\u00e9mission le 19 d\u00e9cembre 1947 : voir {{cite journal|language = fr|first= Dominique |last=Andolfatto|title = Les syndicats en France|journal= \u00c9tudes de la Documentation fran\u00e7aise|issue = 5260|year = 2007|issn = |url = //books.google.fr/books?id=ztILAQAAMAAJ}}</ref> Moreover, Martinez is the first technician, not worker, to lead the union.\n\n[[File:Philippe Martinez.jpg|thumb|Philippe Martinez in 2017.|225px]]\nTo take account of the growing influence of the [[ultra-left]] in the union, Martinez took on a hard line of struggle against employers and [[economic liberalism|liberalism]], notably against the [[Second Valls government|Valls government]] by demanding the withdrawal of the [[El Khomri law|2016 Labour reform bill]], to which the CGT became the main opponent.<ref name=fig/> Demonstrations were accompanied by blockades of refineries, repetitive strikes in the transport sector, and stoppage of nuclear power plants, which threatened the smooth running of the [[UEFA Euro 2016]] in France.<ref name=fig/> The Filpac-CGT (Federation of Workers of the Book, Paper and Communications Industry), demanded that all national daily newspapers publish a column of Philippe Martinez \u2014called {{lang|fr|La modernit\u00e9, c\u2019est le progr\u00e8s social, pas la loi travail !}} (\"Modernity is Social Progress, not Labour Law!\")\u2014, for them to be printed out.<ref name=\"liberation20160526\">{{cite news|language=fr|title=Comment la Filpac-CGT a bloqu\u00e9 la parution des journaux nationaux jeudi|newspaper=Lib\u00e9ration|date=May 26, 2016|url=http://www.liberation.fr/futurs/2016/05/26/comment-la-filpac-cgt-a-bloque-la-parution-des-journaux-nationaux-jeudi_1455346}}</ref><ref name=\"marianne20160526\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Thomas|last=Vampouille|title=Apr\u00e8s l'\u00e9chec de son chantage, la CGT bloque les quotidiens nationaux|newspaper=[[Marianne (magazine)|Marianne]]|date=May 26, 2016|url=https://www.marianne.net/apres-echec-son-chantage-cgt-bloque-les-quotidiens-nationaux-100243150.html}}</ref> Only the newspaper ''[[L'Humanit\u00e9]]'' published the tribune,<ref name=\"lefigaro20160526\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Alexandre |last=Debout\u00e9 |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/medias/2016/05/26/20004-20160526ARTFIG00085-les-quotidiens-nationaux-victimes-d-un-chantage-de-la-cgt.php |title=Les quotidiens nationaux victimes d'un chantage de la CGT |newspaper=[[Le Figaro]] |date=May 26, 2016}}</ref> and the Filipac voted a strike to stop printing the newspapers, which aroused criticism from newspaper leaders and the national daily press union (SPQN), in the name of [[freedom of the press]].<ref name=\"mediapart20160526\">{{cite news|language=fr|first1=Mathilde|last1=Goanec|first2=Micha\u00ebl|last2=Hajdenberg|first3=Dan|last3=Israel|title=Libert\u00e9 de la presse: la CGT n'imprime pas|newspaper=[[Mediapart]]|date=May 26, 2016|url=https://www.mediapart.fr/journal/france/260516/liberte-de-la-presse-la-cgt-nimprime-pas}}</ref><ref name=\"lepoint20160526\">{{cite news|language=fr|title=Pourquoi la CGT emp\u00eache la presse de para\u00eetre|newspaper=[[Le Point]]|date=May 26, 2016|url=http://www.lepoint.fr/medias/pourquoi-la-cgt-empeche-la-presse-de-paraitre-26-05-2016-2042218_260.php}}</ref><ref name=\"valeuractuelles20160526\">{{cite news|language=fr|url=https://www.valeursactuelles.com/societe/censure-de-la-presse-la-cgt-en-pleine-derive-dictatoriale-62155 |title=Censure de la presse : la CGT en pleine d\u00e9rive dictatoriale  |newspaper=[[Valeurs actuelles]]|date=May 26, 2016}}</ref>\n\nFaced with the internal oppositions and the decreasing importance of the CGT in the staff representatives elections, this anti-establishment opinion could enable the union to unify the militants and draw benefit from the left-wing voters' dissatisfaction toward the [[Socialist Party (France)|Socialist Party]] government.<ref name=fig/>\n\nMartinez was re-elected as the general secretary of the CGT during the union's 51st congress in Marseille in April 2016.<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|title=Philippe Martinez r\u00e9\u00e9lu \u00e0 la t\u00eate d'une \"CGT d\u00e9termin\u00e9e\"|url=http://www.liberation.fr/france/2016/04/22/philippe-martinez-reelu-a-la-tete-d-une-cgt-determinee_1447915|date=April 22, 2016|access-date=August 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\nUnder Martinez's chairmanship, in March 2017, the CGT became the second most important union in the [[private sector]] after the [[French Democratic Confederation of Labour]] (CFDT).<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/social/2017/03/31/20011-20170331ARTFIG00091-la-cfdt-pourrait-detroner-la-cgt-et-devenir-le-premier-syndicat-national.php |title=La CFDT d\u00e9tr\u00f4ne la CGT et devient le premier syndicat national dans le priv\u00e9|newspaper=[[Le Figaro]]|date=March 31, 2017}}</ref> However, it remained the largest union in small businesses and in the [[French Civil Service|Civil Service]] and therefore remained the largest organisation among all wage earners.<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|author=|title=Repr\u00e9sentativit\u00e9 syndicale (CGT)|newspaper=[[L'Humanit\u00e9]]|date=March 31, 2017|issn=|url=https://www.humanite.fr/representativite-syndicale-cgt-634179|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nUnder Martinez's direction, the CGT organised a 36-day strike in the first semester 2018 against the government's reform plans of the [[SNCF]].<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|title=Martinez: gr\u00e8ve \"massive\" \u00e0 la SNCF, il faut \"repartir d'une feuille blanche\"|newspaper=[[L'Express]]|date=April 3, 2018|url=https://www.lexpress.fr/actualites/1/politique/martinez-greve-massive-a-la-sncf-il-faut-repartir-d-une-feuille-blanche_1997179.html|access-date=April 3, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019, Martinez was re-elected general secretary of the CGT during the 52nd congress in [[Dijon]]. He was the only candidate to his own succession and was re-elected with 90.65 percent of votes.<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|url=https://www.liberation.fr/france/2019/05/17/reelu-a-la-tete-de-la-cgt-philippe-martinez-appelle-au-rassemblement_1727621 |newspaper=[[Lib\u00e9ration]]|date=May 17, 2019 |title=R\u00e9\u00e9lu \u00e0 la t\u00eate de la CGT Philippe Martinez appelle au \" rassemblement \"|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Opinions==\nWhen he was elected the general secretary of the CGT, Martinez proposed to reduce the weekly work time to 32 hours to enable the creation of four million new jobs.<ref name=\"rtl20150206\">{{cite news|language=fr|first=Fran\u00e7ois |last=Lenglet |author-link=Fran\u00e7ois Lenglet |title=Travail : le leader de la CGT Philippe Martinez plaide pour la semaine de 32 heures |url=http://www.rtl.fr/actu/economie/travail-le-leader-de-la-cgt-philippe-martinez-plaide-pour-la-semaine-de-32-heures-7776493619 |date=February 6, 2015 |publisher=[[RTL (French radio)|RTL]]}}</ref><ref name=\"challenges20150205\">{{cite news|language=fr|title=A peine \u00e9lu \u00e0 la t\u00eate de la CGT, Philippe Martinez plaide pour les 32 heures |url=https://www.challenges.fr/economie/20150205.CHA2809/a-peine-elu-a-la-tete-de-la-cgt-philippe-martinez-plaide-pour-les-32-heures.html |newspaper=[[Challenges (magazine)|Challenges]] |date=February 5, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|language=fr|title=Pour la CGT, passer \u00e0 32 heures est une n\u00e9cessit\u00e9|url=https://www.humanite.fr/pour-la-cgt-passer-32-heures-est-une-necessite-586757|date=October 13, 2015|access-date=August 13, 2016}}</ref> He also supports a \u20ac1800 gross monthly [[minimum wage]], a 60 years old retirement age, and opposes the payment of [[dividends]] to shareholders.<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/politique/article/2019/05/13/martinez-met-en-garde-une-cgt-qui-ne-doit-pas-se-refermer-sur-elle-meme_5461624_823448.html|title=Philippe Martinez met en garde une CGT qui \" ne doit pas se refermer sur elle-m\u00eame \"|newspaper=[[Le Monde]]|date=May 13, 2019|access-date=December 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\nBetween the two rounds of the [[2017 French presidential election]] between [[Emmanuel Macron]] and [[Marine Le Pen]], Martinez claimed he wanted \"Macron to have the highest possible score\" against the [[National Front (France)|National Front]] candidate, thereby overstepping the original position of the GGT.<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/election-presidentielle-2017/article/2017/05/05/martinez-souhaite-que-macron-fasse-le-score-le-plus-haut-possible_5123118_4854003.html |title=Martinez souhaite que \u00ab Macron fasse le score le plus haut possible|newspaper=Le Monde|date=May 5, 2017|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nMartinez supported the welcoming of [[Immigration|migrants]] several time: for instance in 2018, he claimed that it was France's \"duty\" to \"welcome them all\" and considered as \"scandalous\" the government's decision to distinguish [[economic migrant]]s from [[refugees]].<ref>{{cite news|language=fr|url=http://information.tv5monde.com/en-continu/migrants-il-faut-les-accueillir-tous-pour-martinez-214334 |title=Migrants: il faut \"les accueillir tous\" pour Martinez|website=tv5monde.com|date=January 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Private life==\nMartinez lives with Nathalie Gamiochipi, former general secretary of the [[CGT Sant\u00e9]], the second largest federation of the CGT with 75,000 members.<ref name=\"nouvelobs20151019\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Portal|Organised labour|France}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Philippe Martinez}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Martinez, Philippe}}\n[[Category:Members of the General Confederation of Labour (France)]]\n[[Category:Trade union leaders]]\n[[Category:People from Suresnes]]\n[[Category:French people of Spanish descent]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Warofdreams", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eProfessional career:link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippe_Martinez_(trade_unionist)"}
